<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Tornado Cash Laundering Pattern Review</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #090f17;
      --bg-2: #0c1420;
      --panel: #101927;
      --panel-2: #142133;
      --line: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      --text: #f3f7fc;
      --muted: #aab7ca;
      --muted-2: #8ea0b7;
      --accent: #4ea1ff;
      --accent-soft: rgba(78,161,255,0.12);
      --green: #49d18f;
      --green-soft: rgba(73,209,143,0.12);
      --yellow: #ffd35c;
      --yellow-soft: rgba(255,211,92,0.12);
      --red: #ff7c86;
      --red-soft: rgba(255,124,134,0.12);
      --violet: #b479ff;
      --shadow: 0 18px 44px rgba(0,0,0,0.34);
      --radius: 18px;
      --max: 1220px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body {
      font-family: Inter, Arial, sans-serif;
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(78,161,255,0.14), transparent 22%),
        radial-gradient(circle at 20% 0%, rgba(180,121,255,0.08), transparent 18%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg) 0%, var(--bg-2) 100%);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .container {
      width: min(var(--max), calc(100% - 32px));
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 44px 0 28px;
    }

    .hero-card {
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 28px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(20,33,51,0.96) 0%, rgba(16,25,39,0.98) 100%);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 32px;
    }

    .hero-card::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background-image:
        linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 1px, transparent 1px),
        linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 1px, transparent 1px);
      background-size: 60px 60px;
      mask-image: radial-gradient(circle at 70% 35%, black 18%, transparent 72%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    h1, h2, h3, h4 { line-height: 1.15; }
    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(34px, 4.7vw, 54px);
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1.15fr 0.85fr;
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: start;
    }

    .hero-copy p {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 17px;
      max-width: 760px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .tag-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .tag {
      padding: 8px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      color: #dbe6f8;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .meta-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 14px;
    }

    .meta-box {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      padding: 16px;
    }

    .meta-box span {
      display: block;
      color: var(--muted-2);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      font-size: 11px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .meta-box strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 15px;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .layout {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      align-items: start;
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }

    .sidebar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 18px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 20px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--panel) 0%, var(--panel-2) 100%);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 20px;
    }

    .sidebar h3 {
      font-size: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .sidebar a {
      display: block;
      color: #d8e4f7;
      padding: 10px 12px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid transparent;
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .sidebar a:hover {
      text-decoration: none;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border-color: var(--line);
    }

    .content {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 22px;
    }

    .card {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--panel) 0%, var(--panel-2) 100%);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .card h2 {
      font-size: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .card h3 {
      font-size: 19px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .card p {
      color: var(--muted);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .grid-2, .grid-3, .visual-grid, .metrics-grid, .flag-grid {
      display: grid;
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .grid-2, .visual-grid, .metrics-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
    .grid-3, .flag-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); }

    .tile {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      padding: 18px;
    }

    .tile small {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      color: #b8c7db;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      font-size: 11px;
    }

    .tile strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .tile p { margin: 0; font-size: 15px; }

    .metric {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: space-between;
      min-height: 132px;
    }

    .metric .value {
      font-size: 32px;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
      margin-top: 6px;
    }

    .metric .sub {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .expansion-banner {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 18px;
      padding: 18px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,211,92,0.22);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,211,92,0.12) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 100%);
    }

    .expansion-block {
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      text-align: center;
    }

    .expansion-block span {
      display: block;
      font-size: 12px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      color: var(--muted-2);
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .expansion-block strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 32px;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .expansion-arrow {
      font-size: 28px;
      color: var(--yellow);
      font-weight: 800;
    }

    .flow {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .flow-step {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      color: #ebf2fd;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    .flow-arrow {
      align-self: center;
      font-size: 18px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .section-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .list-item {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
      align-items: start;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      padding: 16px;
    }

    .icon {
      width: 40px;
      height: 40px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #08111a;
    }

    .blue { background: var(--accent); }
    .green { background: var(--green); }
    .yellow { background: var(--yellow); }
    .red { background: var(--red); }
    .violet { background: var(--violet); }

    .evidence-strip {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-top: 14px;
    }

    .pill {
      padding: 8px 12px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 13px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      color: #dce7f8;
    }

    .pill.green { background: var(--green-soft); color: #c9f7e0; border-color: rgba(73,209,143,0.22); }
    .pill.yellow { background: var(--yellow-soft); color: #fff0be; border-color: rgba(255,211,92,0.22); }
    .pill.red { background: var(--red-soft); color: #ffd4d8; border-color: rgba(255,124,134,0.22); }

    .image-card {
      overflow: hidden;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .image-wrap {
      position: relative;
      background: #0a1018;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    .image-wrap img {
      width: 100%;
      display: block;
      height: auto;
    }

    .image-badge {
      position: absolute;
      top: 14px;
      left: 14px;
      padding: 7px 11px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(10,15,23,0.86);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      color: #d8e6fb;
      font-size: 12px;
    }

    .image-body {
      padding: 18px 18px 20px;
    }

    .caption {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .flag {
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 18px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    }

    .flag.high { background: var(--red-soft); border-color: rgba(255,124,134,0.22); }
    .flag.medium { background: var(--yellow-soft); border-color: rgba(255,211,92,0.22); }
    .flag.low { background: var(--green-soft); border-color: rgba(73,209,143,0.22); }

    .flag .level {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 6px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 11px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
    }

    .flag h4 {
      font-size: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .flag p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .conclusion-box {
      border: 1px solid rgba(73,209,143,0.22);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(73,209,143,0.12) 0%, rgba(255,255,255,0.02) 100%);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 20px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .footer-nav {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin: 8px 0 50px;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 13px 18px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(78,161,255,0.18), rgba(78,161,255,0.08));
      color: #fff;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .btn.secondary {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
    }

    @media (max-width: 980px) {
      .hero-grid, .layout, .grid-2, .grid-3, .visual-grid, .metrics-grid, .flag-grid, .expansion-banner {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
      .sidebar { position: static; }
      .expansion-banner { display: block; }
      .expansion-arrow { display: block; text-align: center; margin: 12px 0; }
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .hero-card, .card, .sidebar { padding: 18px; }
      .meta-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      h1 { font-size: 32px; }
      .card h2 { font-size: 24px; }
      .flow { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
      .flow-arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-card">
        <div class="hero-grid">
          <div class="hero-copy">
            <h1>Tornado Cash Laundering Pattern Review</h1>
            <p>
              This case began with two Tornado Cash withdrawals that appeared limited to a standard fixed-denomination pattern. On initial review, the visible value appeared to be only 200 ETH.
            </p>
            <p>
              After deeper cluster analysis, the case expanded into a much larger laundering ecosystem, revealing approximately 7,369 ETH of related activity across linked wallets and non-custodial exchange routing pathways.
            </p>
            <div class="tag-row">
              <div class="tag">Mixer Analysis</div>
              <div class="tag">Cluster Expansion</div>
              <div class="tag">Layering Review</div>
              <div class="tag">AML Risk Assessment</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="meta-grid">
            <div class="meta-box">
              <span>Starting Point</span>
              <strong>2 Tornado Cash Withdrawals</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-box">
              <span>Surface Value</span>
              <strong>200 ETH</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-box">
              <span>Cluster Value</span>
              <strong>~7,369 ETH</strong>
            </div>
            <div class="meta-box">
              <span>Non-Custodial Deposit Points</span>
              <strong>16 Identified Addresses</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="expansion-banner">
          <div class="expansion-block">
            <span>Initial Visible Activity</span>
            <strong>200 ETH</strong>
          </div>
          <div class="expansion-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="expansion-block">
            <span>Deeper Cluster Exposure</span>
            <strong>~7,369 ETH</strong>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="layout">
      <aside class="sidebar">
        <h3>Report Navigation</h3>
        <a href="#dashboard">Dashboard</a>
        <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="#surface-analysis">Surface Analysis</a>
        <a href="#deep-analysis">Deep Analysis</a>
        <a href="#methodology">Methodology</a>
        <a href="#pattern">Laundering Pattern</a>
        <a href="#findings">Key Findings</a>
        <a href="#risk-flags">Risk Flags</a>
        <a href="#screenshots">Screenshots</a>
        <a href="#conclusion">Conclusion</a>
      </aside>

      <div class="content">
        <section id="dashboard" class="card">
          <h2>Investigation Dashboard</h2>
          <p>
            High-level summary of the laundering structure, expansion in exposure, and routing behavior observed during the analysis.
          </p>
          <div class="metrics-grid">
            <div class="tile metric">
              <small>Seed Transactions</small>
              <div class="value">2</div>
              <div class="sub">The investigation started from two linked Tornado Cash withdrawals</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tile metric">
              <small>Initial Visible Value</small>
              <div class="value">200</div>
              <div class="sub">ETH visible from the first two withdrawals alone</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tile metric">
              <small>Expanded Cluster Value</small>
              <div class="value">7,369</div>
              <div class="sub">Approximate ETH revealed through deeper clustering and flow review</div>
            </div>
            <div class="tile metric">
              <small>Deposit Points</small>
              <div class="value">16</div>
              <div class="sub">Addresses used to route assets through automated non-custodial instant exchanges</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="evidence-strip">
            <div class="pill red">Mixer usage</div>
            <div class="pill yellow">Layering pattern</div>
            <div class="pill yellow">Rapid dispersion</div>
            <div class="pill red">Non-custodial exchange routing</div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="overview" class="card">
          <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
          <p>
            This investigation began with two Tornado Cash withdrawal transactions, each reflecting a standard 100 ETH withdrawal pattern. At surface level, the case appeared limited to 200 ETH.
          </p>
          <p>
            However, deeper cluster analysis showed that these two withdrawals were only the visible entry points into a broader laundering ecosystem. By tracing linked wallets, fund flow relationships, and routing behavior, the total exposure expanded to approximately 7,369 ETH.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2">
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Main Insight</small>
              <strong>Surface visibility can be misleading</strong>
              <p>The first two withdrawals alone understate the real scale of the laundering activity.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Analytical Value</small>
              <strong>Cluster analysis reveals hidden scale</strong>
              <p>Linked wallet and ecosystem review exposed a much larger network of related movement.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="surface-analysis" class="card">
          <h2>Initial Observation (Surface Analysis)</h2>
          <p>
            The case started from two Tornado Cash withdrawal events, each associated with the 100 ETH denomination pool. This produced an immediate visible total of 200 ETH.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2">
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Surface Finding</small>
              <strong>2 withdrawals × 100 ETH</strong>
              <p>At the beginning of the review, the case appeared to be limited to a standard 200 ETH withdrawal pattern.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Interpretation</small>
              <strong>Potential underestimation</strong>
              <p>Without deeper graph and cluster analysis, the broader laundering ecosystem would remain hidden.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="deep-analysis" class="card">
          <h2>Cluster-Based Deep Analysis</h2>
          <p>
            Deeper analysis using graph relationships and address clustering revealed that the case extended far beyond the initial two withdrawals. The identified laundering ecosystem expanded to approximately 7,369 ETH in total observed activity.
          </p>
          <div class="grid-2">
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Key Insight</small>
              <strong>200 ETH → ~7,369 ETH</strong>
              <p>The visible withdrawals represented only a small portion of the total laundering exposure uncovered through cluster analysis.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Why It Matters</small>
              <strong>Hidden scale of laundering</strong>
              <p>This demonstrates how advanced blockchain analysis can materially change the understanding of a case’s true size and complexity.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="methodology" class="card">
          <h2>Methodology</h2>
          <p>
            The investigation combined transaction validation, graph analysis, and clustering review to determine recipient behavior, uncover linked counterparties, and quantify the broader laundering network.
          </p>
          <div class="section-list">
            <div class="list-item">
              <div class="icon blue">1</div>
              <div>
                <h3>Recipient Identification</h3>
                <p>Withdrawal recipient addresses were identified from Tornado Cash input data and validated through transaction logs, without relying on visible wallet labels alone.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="list-item">
              <div class="icon green">2</div>
              <div>
                <h3>Surface Transaction Validation</h3>
                <p>Initial withdrawal values were confirmed using Tornado Cash denomination behavior and blockchain explorer review.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="list-item">
              <div class="icon yellow">3</div>
              <div>
                <h3>Cluster Expansion</h3>
                <p>MetaSleuth graph analysis and Arkham ecosystem review were used to identify linked wallets and the broader laundering structure.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="list-item">
              <div class="icon violet">4</div>
              <div>
                <h3>Deposit Point Analysis</h3>
                <p>Final routing behavior revealed 16 addresses used to launder assets through automated non-custodial instant exchange pathways.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="pattern" class="card">
          <h2>Laundering Pattern Identified</h2>
          <p>
            The case reveals a structured laundering pattern in which funds are withdrawn from a mixer, dispersed across linked wallets, and routed into non-custodial exchange mechanisms to further obscure provenance.
          </p>
          <div class="flow">
            <div class="flow-step">Tornado Cash Withdrawal</div>
            <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="flow-step">Recipient Wallets</div>
            <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="flow-step">Clustered Counterparties</div>
            <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="flow-step">Intermediary Distribution</div>
            <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="flow-step">Non-Custodial Exchange Routing</div>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-3">
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Stage 1</small>
              <strong>Mixer Exit</strong>
              <p>Two withdrawals created the visible entry point into the case.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Stage 2</small>
              <strong>Graph Expansion</strong>
              <p>Linked counterparties revealed a much larger web of related addresses.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Stage 3</small>
              <strong>Layering via Exchanges</strong>
              <p>Funds moved through 16 identified deposit points associated with non-custodial instant exchange behavior.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="findings" class="card">
          <h2>Key Findings</h2>
          <div class="grid-2">
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Misleading Surface Value</small>
              <strong>Initial visible activity showed only 200 ETH</strong>
              <p>The first two withdrawals alone did not reveal the full scope of the case.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>True Exposure</small>
              <strong>Cluster analysis revealed ~7,369 ETH</strong>
              <p>Deeper analysis uncovered materially larger linked activity across the laundering ecosystem.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Routing Structure</small>
              <strong>16 non-custodial deposit points identified</strong>
              <p>The laundering flow used multiple addresses associated with automated instant exchange pathways.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <small>Analytical Outcome</small>
              <strong>Structured laundering network</strong>
              <p>The overall pattern is consistent with deliberate layering and obfuscation rather than isolated transfers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="risk-flags" class="card">
          <h2>Risk Indicators</h2>
          <p>
            The following indicators are relevant from an AML, transaction monitoring, and blockchain investigation perspective.
          </p>
          <div class="flag-grid">
            <div class="flag high">
              <div class="level">High</div>
              <h4>Mixer Usage</h4>
              <p>Use of Tornado Cash is a direct obfuscation indicator and is commonly associated with high-risk laundering typologies.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flag high">
